{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778984995378,"sessionID":"ses_1cc4a8d68ffeVLcqS32UKOLNd6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_d5zXU1ncymS6ZgBwdH69M6X2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0003400` (`regulation of COPII vesicle coating`) with `replaced_by: GO:0048208`.\n+- Renamed `GO:0048208` from `COPII vesicle coating` to `COPII vesicle coat assembly`.\n+- Renamed `GO:0006901` from `vesicle coating` to `vesicle coat assembly`.\n+\n+I preserved the former labels as exact synonyms on the retained terms where appropriate, and validated the ontology after the edits with `make travis_build`.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Summary\n+\n+This change addresses issue `#31945` by obsoleting `GO:0003400 regulation of COPII vesicle coating` and updating the relevant retained process terms to use the clearer `coat assembly` wording requested in the issue discussion.\n+\n+Changes made\n+\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0003400 regulation of COPII vesicle coating`.\n+- Added `replaced_by: GO:0048208`.\n+- Added a term tracker link to `https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31945`.\n+- Removed the obsolete term's logical axioms and retained only historical provenance plus obsoletion metadata, following GO obsoletion conventions.\n+- Renamed `GO:0048208` from `COPII vesicle coating` to `COPII vesicle coat assembly`.\n+- Updated the `GO:0048208` definition to align with the new label.\n+- Converted the previous primary label `COPII vesicle coating` into an exact synonym.\n+- Renamed `GO:0006901` from `vesicle coating` to `vesicle coat assembly`.\n+- Updated the `GO:0006901` definition to align with the new label.\n+- Converted the previous broad synonym arrangement so that `vesicle coating` is now retained as an exact synonym of `GO:0006901`.\n+- Updated the parent label reference on `GO:0048208` accordingly.\n+\n+Rationale\n+\n+The issue states that annotations to `GO:0003400` are better described as being part of the vesicle coating pathway itself rather than upstream regulation. That makes direct replacement with `GO:0048208` appropriate. The issue comments also explicitly requested renaming `GO:0048208` and `GO:0006901` to use `coat assembly`, which better matches the biology and was already reflected in existing synonym usage.\n+\n+Validation\n+\n+- Pre-validation completed successfully with `cd src/ontology && make travis_build` before edits.\n+- Post-edit validation completed successfully with `cd src/ontology && make travis_build` after check-in.\n+\n+Checklist\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: Issue context reviewed and requested actions were clear.\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Ontology validated before edits.\n+- [ ] RESEARCH: Not needed for this direct obsoletion and label cleanup.\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Inspected the affected terms and related references in `go-edit.obo`.\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Reviewed relevant naming/obsoletion expectations and existing term precedent.\n+- [x] EDITS: Used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow.\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Removed obsolete-term axioms; retained live-term relationships and updated parent label references only.\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: Used term obsoletion guidance.\n+- [x] METADATA: Added obsoletion metadata and issue tracker link; no new terms created.\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes.\n+- [ ] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: No new literature references introduced.\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Ontology edit committed locally.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0003400` (`regulation of COPII vesicle coating`) with `replaced_by: GO:0048208`.\n+- Renamed `GO:0048208` from `COPII vesicle coating` to `COPII vesicle coat assembly`.\n+- Renamed `GO:0006901` from `vesicle coating` to `vesicle coat assembly`.\n+\n+I preserved the former labels as exact synonyms on the retained terms where appropriate, and validated the ontology after the edits with `make travis_build`.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+Summary\n+\n+This change addresses issue `#31945` by obsoleting `GO:0003400 regulation of COPII vesicle coating` and updating the relevant retained process terms to use the clearer `coat assembly` wording requested in the issue discussion.\n+\n+Changes made\n+\n+- Obsoleted `GO:0003400 regulation of COPII vesicle coating`.\n+- Added `replaced_by: GO:0048208`.\n+- Added a term tracker link to `https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31945`.\n+- Removed the obsolete term's logical axioms and retained only historical provenance plus obsoletion metadata, following GO obsoletion conventions.\n+- Renamed `GO:0048208` from `COPII vesicle coating` to `COPII vesicle coat assembly`.\n+- Updated the `GO:0048208` definition to align with the new label.\n+- Converted the previous primary label `COPII vesicle coating` into an exact synonym.\n+- Renamed `GO:0006901` from `vesicle coating` to `vesicle coat assembly`.\n+- Updated the `GO:0006901` definition to align with the new label.\n+- Converted the previous broad synonym arrangement so that `vesicle coating` is now retained as an exact synonym of `GO:0006901`.\n+- Updated the parent label reference on `GO:0048208` accordingly.\n+\n+Rationale\n+\n+The issue states that annotations to `GO:0003400` are better described as being part of the vesicle coating pathway itself rather than upstream regulation. That makes direct replacement with `GO:0048208` appropriate. The issue comments also explicitly requested renaming `GO:0048208` and `GO:0006901` to use `coat assembly`, which better matches the biology and was already reflected in existing synonym usage.\n+\n+Validation\n+\n+- Pre-validation completed successfully with `cd src/ontology && make travis_build` before edits.\n+- Post-edit validation completed successfully with `cd src/ontology && make travis_build` after check-in.\n+\n+Checklist\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: Issue context reviewed and requested actions were clear.\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Ontology validated before edits.\n+- [ ] RESEARCH: Not needed for this direct obsoletion and label cleanup.\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Inspected the affected terms and related references in `go-edit.obo`.\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Reviewed relevant naming/obsoletion expectations and existing term precedent.\n+- [x] EDITS: Used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow.\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Removed obsolete-term axioms; retained live-term relationships and updated parent label references only.\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: Used term obsoletion guidance.\n+- [x] METADATA: Added obsoletion metadata and issue tracker link; no new terms created.\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes.\n+- [ ] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: No new literature references introduced.\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Ontology edit committed locally.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/